Two people died along the Nairobi-Mombasa Road in Athi River after a Mash Poa bus was involved in a head-on collision with a lorry. Other passengers were injured, two of them seriously. Athi River deputy police boss Salim Komora told the Star on the phone the accident occurred in the wee hours of Sunday morning. Police blame the lorry driver for causing the crash. The bus was heading from Mombasa to Nairobi, police reports indicate. The lorry was going in the opposite direction. Police said the injured were taken to Shalom Community Hospital and Machakos Level 5 Hospital where they are being treated. The bodies were taken to Shalom Community Hospital mortuary. The vehicles were towed to the police station. Click here for the latest political news   